msgid "&productname; provides a script to clean up configuration that is unique to each installation. With the introduction of systemd, unique system identifiers are used and set in different locations and files. Therefore, cloning is no longer the recommended way to build system images. Images can be created with &kiwi;, see <link xlink:href=\"https://doc.opensuse.org/projects/kiwi/doc/\"></link>."
